            "text": "Cytokine storm during viral infection is a prospective predictor of morbidity and mortality ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "yet the cellular sources remain undefined . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "Here , using genetic and chemical tools",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "to probe functions of the S1P 1 receptor ,",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "we elucidate cellular and signaling mechanisms",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "that are important in initiating cytokine storm . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Whereas S1P 1 receptor is expressed on endothelial cells and lymphocytes within lung tissue ,",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "S1P 1 agonism suppresses cytokines and innate immune cell recruitment in wild - type and lymphocyte - deficient mice ,",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "identifying endothelial cells as central regulators of cytokine storm . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Furthermore , our data reveal immune cell infiltration and cytokine production as distinct events",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "that are both orchestrated by endothelial cells . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Moreover , we demonstrate",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "that suppression of early innate immune responses through S1P 1 signaling results in reduced mortality during infection with a human pathogenic strain of influenza virus . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "Modulation of endothelium with a specific agonist suggests",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "that diseases",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "in which amplification of cytokine storm is a significant pathological component",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
